#. type: Title #
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Working with forms"
msgid "Working on Windows"
msgstr "使用表单"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "Yii applications usually run on Linux in production. On Windows, choose a local workflow that stays close to that environment and keeps filesystem performance predictable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Recommended setup: WSL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "Use [Windows Subsystem for Linux](https://learn.microsoft.com/windows/wsl/) with a Linux distribution such as Ubuntu.  Install PHP, Composer, Git, and Make inside WSL, then clone the project into the Linux filesystem:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (shell)
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"cd ~\n"
"git clone https://github.com/yiisoft/app.git my-app\n"
"cd my-app\n"
"composer install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "Keep the project under the WSL filesystem, for example `/home/user/projects/my-app`. Avoid working from a mounted Windows path such as `/mnt/c/Users/user/projects/my-app`; it is much slower for Composer, tests, and tools that read many small files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "You can open the project from Windows editors through the WSL integration. In PhpStorm, open the project from the WSL filesystem. In VS Code, use the WSL extension and open the folder from inside the WSL session."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Docker with WSL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "Docker Desktop with the WSL backend is also a good Windows setup. Keep the project in the WSL filesystem and run Docker commands from WSL:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (shell)
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"make build\n"
"make up\n"
"make yii\n"
"make test\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "This keeps bind mounts fast and gives containers Linux paths that match the tooling used by the Yii application templates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "If you need IDE links from debug stack traces, set `APP_HOST_PATH` to the project path that your IDE can open."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Git Bash"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "[Git for Windows](https://git-scm.com/downloads/win) installs Git Bash and common Unix tools. It can be enough when you want to run the application directly on Windows without WSL or Docker."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "Use this option when your project does not depend on Linux-only extensions or shell scripts. Check the same commands you expect contributors to use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (shell)
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"composer install\n"
"composer test\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "If the project uses `make`, Git for Windows includes a Bash environment, but `make` availability depends on your local installation. Install it separately when needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "PowerShell and CMD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "PowerShell and CMD can run PHP and Composer, but they differ from the common Linux server environment in quoting, environment variables, paths, and shell utilities. Use them for simple commands only."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "For regular Yii development on Windows, prefer WSL or Docker with WSL."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "Choosing a workflow"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "Use WSL when you want the closest local match to a Linux server and do not need containers for every service."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "Use Docker with WSL when you want the application, database, and other services described by Compose files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "Use Git Bash for small projects or quick checks that run directly on Windows."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/cookbook/working-on-windows.md
msgid "Use PowerShell or CMD when the command is known to be platform-neutral."
msgstr ""
